   any existing copyright or license notice in the files.

4. **Derivative works (including 二次开发 by other universities).**  If You publicly
   distribute a modified version (including forks adapted for another university):
   (i) You must prominently state that the work is derived from swuthesis and name
       the Author;
   (ii) You must document the nature of Your changes (e.g. README or changelog);
   (iii) You must not represent Your derivative as the original swuthesis without
        distinction; use a distinct project name when the product is no longer
        substantially the same template;
   (iv) This license does **not** grant any trademark or university-name rights beyond
        what is required for honest attribution.

5. **Institutional adoption and author’s funding rights.**  Adoption or endorsement
